# ============================================================
#  Whitelist .gitignore  —  "ignore everything, keep only code"
# ------------------------------------------------------------
#  Line 1 ignores EVERYTHING. The `!` lines below re-include
#  the file types we DO want to track. Because the bulk data
#  and tool outputs are never re-included, they can never be
#  committed by accident — even brand-new output dirs.
#
#  All code in this project lives in the repo root, so we only
#  re-include root-level *.py / *.sh / *.md. Files with those
#  extensions *inside* ignored directories stay ignored.
# ============================================================

# 1) Ignore everything by default
*

# 2) Re-include the code and docs we want under version control
!.gitignore
!*.py
!*.sh
!*.md

# ---
# If you ever add a code subdirectory (e.g. src/), you must also
# un-ignore the directory before git will descend into it, e.g.:
#   !src/
#   !src/**/*.py
